<refnamediv><indexterm><primary sortas="enable-http-lb-application">enable-http-lb-application &mdash;
enables a previously-disabled application managed by a load balancer</primary>
</indexterm><indexterm><primary sortas="enables a previously-disabled application managed by a load balancer">
enables a previously-disabled application managed by a load balancer &mdash;
enable-http-lb-application</primary></indexterm><refname>enable-http-lb-application
</refname><refpurpose>enables a previously-disabled application managed by
a load balancer</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>&synp-tt;</title>
<cmdsynopsis><command>enable-http-lb-application</command>&synopsis-common;
<arg choice="plain"><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;name <replaceable>application_name
</replaceable></option></arg><arg choice="plain"><replaceable>target</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1><title>&desc-tt;</title>
<para>When applications are deployed, by default they are disabled for load
balancing. Use this command to enable applications deployed on a stand-alone
instance or cluster for load balancing. Enable the application on all instances
in a cluster, or on a single standalone server instance.</para>
</refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&opts-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="medium">&options-common;
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;name</option></term>
<listitem><para>The name of the application to be enabled.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&oper-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="medium">
<varlistentry><term><replaceable>target</replaceable></term><listitem><para>
This operand specifies on which server instance or cluster to enable the application.
Valid values are:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><replaceable>cluster_name</replaceable>, which enables the
application on all server instances in the cluster.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><replaceable>stand-alone_instance_name</replaceable>, which
enables the application in the stand-<?Pub Caret>alone server instance.</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist></para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&exam-tt;</title>
<example>
<title>Using the enable-http-lb-server command</title>
<screen>asadmin> <userinput>enable-http-lb-application --user admin 
--passwordfile password.txt --name webapps-simple mycluster

</userinput>
Command enable-http-lb-application executed successfully.

</screen>
</example>
</refsect1>
